<div class="card shadow-sm border-0 rounded-4 mb-5">
    <div class="card-body p-4">
        <h2 class="h5 fw-bold mb-3 text-dark">Comment Module</h2>
        <p class="text-muted small">Manage user comments on posts using public and secured endpoints. Includes soft deletion and user-level permission checks.</p>

        <div class="alert alert-warning small p-3 mb-4">
            🔐 <strong>Authorization Info:</strong><br />
            <ul class="mb-0 small">
                <li>
                    <code>GET /api/post/{postId}/comments</code> is <strong>publicly accessible</strong> (no JWT required), but will use the JWT if available to personalize the response (e.g., user reactions).<br />
                    This endpoint still <strong>requires</strong>:
                    <ul>
                        <li><code>X-Tenant-Id</code></li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    All other endpoints (<code>POST</code>, <code>PUT</code>, <code>DELETE</code>) require:
                    <ul>
                        <li>JWT Bearer token</li>
                        <li><code>X-Tenant-Id</code></li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-3">
            <h5 class="fw-semibold text-dark small">Public Endpoint</h5>
            <p class="small mb-2">
                <code>GET /api/post/{postId}/comments</code> — Fetch all comments related to a specific post.
            </p>

            <p class="fw-semibold small mb-1">Example Request:</p>
            <code class="small d-block mb-1">
                GET /api/post/ad70c08c-e0a7-4652-a5c8-60f3269e0992/comments
            </code>
            <div class="text-muted small">
                with headers:
                <code>X-Tenant-Id</code>
            </div>

            <p class="fw-semibold small mt-3 mb-1">Response:</p>
            <pre class="bg-light p-2 small rounded mb-0 small">
[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "postId": 123,
    "content": "Great post!",
    "createdAt": "2025-07-19T14:30:00Z",
    "user": {
      "id": 456,
      "username": "john_doe",
      ...
    }
  },
  ...
]
            </pre>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-4">
            <h5 class="fw-semibold text-dark small">Secured Endpoints</h5>
            <p class="small">Require both JWT and API credentials.</p>

            <div class="mb-3">
                <strong class="small">POST /api/post/{postId}/comments</strong><br />
                <p class="small mb-1">Create a new comment.</p>
                <table class="table table-sm table-bordered small">
                    <thead class="table-light small">
                        <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr><td><code>content</code></td><td>string</td><td>The comment text (required)</td></tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-3">
                <strong class="small">PUT /api/post/{postId}/comments/{commentId}</strong><br />
                <p class="small mb-1">Update a comment.</p>
                <table class="table table-sm table-bordered small">
                    <thead class="table-light small">
                        <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr><td><code>content</code></td><td>string</td><td>The comment text (required)</td></tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-3">
                <strong class="small">DELETE /api/comments/{id}</strong><br />
                <p class="small mb-1">Soft delete a comment by ID (owner or admin only).</p>
            </div>

            <p class="fw-semibold small mb-1">Example Headers:</p>
            <pre class="bg-light p-2 small rounded mb-0">
Authorization: Bearer &lt;your-jwt-token&gt;
X-Tenant-Id: your-tenant-id
Content-Type: application/json
            </pre>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


